         <abstract label="Abstract:">Minutes of the Hospital Board and Section Chief meetings, as
            well as the annual "Student Protocol," a handbook of policies and procedures for fourth
            year DVM students, and one videocassette from the Cornell University College of
            Veterinary Medicine Equine Performance Testing Unit. Also brochures from the hospital.</abstract>
         <langmaterial label="Language:">Collection material in <language encodinganalog="041" langcode="eng">English</language>
         </langmaterial>
      </did>
      <bioghist>
         <head>ORGANIZATIONAL HISTORY</head>
         <p>The Cornell University Hospital for Animals (CUHA) is a unit of the Cornell University
            College of Veterinary Medicine. It comprises the Companion Animal Hospital, the Equine
            Hospital and the Farm Animal Hospital. Specialized units within the hospital include
            Wildlife and Exotic Animal Medicine, Ambulatory and Production Medicine, and Behavioral
            Medicine. It is currently housed in the Veterinary Education Center, which was opened in
            1996. It was formerly named the Cornell University Veterinary Medical Teaching Hospital,
            but was renamed in 2000.</p>
      </bioghist>
      <scopecontent>
         <head>COLLECTION DESCRIPTION</head>
         <p>This collection includes minutes of the Hospital Board and Section Chief meetings, as
            well as the annual "Student Protocol," a handbook of policies and procedures for fourth
            year DVM students, and one videocassette from the Cornell University College of
            Veterinary Medicine Equine Performance Testing Unit. Also brochures from the hospital.</p>
         <p>Also photographs and slides.</p>
      </scopecontent>
